: WordPress 2.6 |publisher=WordPress.org |accessdate=June 15, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100713090059/http://wordpress.org/news/2008/07/wordpress-26-tyner/ |archive-date=July 13, 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| Added new features that made WordPress a more powerful CMS: it can now [[revision control|track changes]] to every post and page and allow easy posting from anywhere on the web.\n|- valign=top\n! {{Version |o |2.7}}\n| ''[[John Coltrane|Coltrane]]''\n| December 11, 2008<ref>{{cite web |url=https://wordpress.org/news/2008/12/coltrane/ |title=WordPress Blog: WordPress 2.7 |publisher=WordPress.org |accessdate=December 11, 2008 |date=2008-12-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100714182948/http://wordpress.org/news/2008/12/coltrane/ |archive-date=July 14, 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| Administration interface redesigned fully, added automatic upgrades and installing plugins, from within the administration interface.\n|- valign=top\n! {{Version |o |2.8}}\n| ''[[Chet Baker|Baker]]''\n| June 10, 2009<ref>{{cite web |url=https://wordpress.org/news/2009/06/wordpress-28/ |title=WordPress Blog: WordPress 2.8 |publisher=WordPress.org |accessdate=June 10, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100714182956/http://wordpress.org/news/2009/06/wordpress-28/ |archive-date=July 14, 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| Added improvements in speed, automatic installing of themes from within administration interface, introduces the CodePress editor for [[syntax highlighting]] and a redesigned widget interface.\n|- valign=top\n! {{Version |o |2.9}}\n| ''[[Carmen McRae|Carmen]]''\n| December 19, 2009<ref>{{cite web |url=https://wordpress.org/news/2009/12/wordpress-2-9/ |title=WordPress Blog: WordPress 2.9 |publisher=WordPress.org |accessdate=December 19, 2009 |date=2009-12-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100713090118/http://wordpress.org/news/2009/12/wordpress-2-9/ |archive-date=July 13, 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| Added global undo, built-in image editor, batch plugin updating, and many less visible tweaks.\n|- valign=top\n| colspan=\"4\" |\n|- valign=top\n! {{Version |o |3.0}}\n| ''[[Thelonious Monk|Thelonious]]''\n| June 17, 2010<ref>{{cite web |url=https://wordpress.org/news/2010/06/thelonious/ |title=WordPress Blog: WordPress 3.0 |publisher=WordPress.org |accessdate=June 17, 2010 |date=2010-06-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100712143344/http://wordpress.org/news/2010/06/thelonious/ |archive-date=July 12, 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| Added a new theme [[application programming interface|APIs]], merge WordPress and WordPress MU, creating the new multi-site functionality, new default theme \"Twenty Ten\" and a refreshed, lighter admin UI.\n|- valign=top\n! {{Version |o |3.1}}\n| ''[[Django Reinhardt|Reinhardt]]''\n| February 23, 2011<ref>{{cite web |url=https://wordpress.org/news/2011/02/threeone/ |title=WordPress Blog: WordPress 3.1 |publisher=WordPress.org |accessdate=February 25, 2011 |date=2011-02-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110224192910/http://wordpress.org/news/2011/02/threeone/ |archive-date=February 24, 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| Added the Admin Bar, which is displayed on all blog pages when an admin is logged in, and Post Format, best explained as a Tumblr like micro-blogging feature. It provides easy access to many critical functions, such as comments and updates. Includes internal linking abilities, a newly streamlined writing interface, and many other changes.\n|- valign=top\n! {{Version |o |3.2}}\n| ''[[George Gershwin|Gershwin]]''\n| July 4, 2011<ref>{{cite web |url=https://wordpress.org/news/2011/07/gershwin/ |title=WordPress Blog: WordPress 3.2 |publisher=WordPress.org |accessdate=June 4, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110705201902/http://wordpress.org/news/2011/07/gershwin/ |archive-date=July 5, 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| Focused on making WordPress faster and lighter. Released only four months after version 3.1, reflecting the growing speed of development in the WordPress community.\n|- valign=top\n! {{Version |o |3.3}}\n| ''[[Sonny Stitt|Sonny]]''\n| December 12, 2011<ref>{{cite web |url=https://wordpress.org/news/2011/12/sonny/ |title=WordPress Blog: WordPress 3.3 |publisher=WordPress.org |accessdate=December 12, 2011 |date=2011-12-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111213220630/http://wordpress.org/news/2011/12/sonny/ |archive-date=December 13, 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| Focused on making WordPress friendlier for beginners and [[tablet computer]] users.\n|- valign=top\n! {{Version |o |3.4}}\n| ''[[Grant Green|Green]]''\n| June 13, 2012<ref>{{cite web |url=https://wordpress.org/news/2012/06/green/ |title=WordPress Blog: WordPress 3.4 |publisher=WordPress.org |accessdate=June 13, 2012 |date=2012-06-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120613214721/http://wordpress.org/news/2012/06/green/ |archive-date=June 13, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| Focused on improvements to theme customization, [[Twitter]] integration and several minor changes.\n|- valign=top\n! {{Version |o |3.5}}\n| ''[[Elvin Jones|Elvin]]''\n| December 11, 2012<ref>{{cite web |url=https://wordpress.org/news/2012/12/elvin/ |title=WordPress Blog: WordPress 3.5 |publisher=WordPress.org |accessdate=December 11, 2012 |date=2012-12-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121211191952/http://wordpress.org/news/2012/12/elvin/ |archive-date=December 11, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| Support for the [[Retina Display]], color picker, new default theme \"Twenty Twelve\", improved image workflow.\n|- valign=top\n! {{Version |o |3.6}}\n| ''[[Oscar Peterson|Oscar]]''\n| August 1, 2013<ref>{{cite web |url=https://wordpress.org/news/2013/08/oscar/ |title=WordPress Blog: WordPress 3.6 |publisher=WordPress.org |accessdate=August 1, 2013 |date=August 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130802010334/http://wordpress.org/news/2013/08/oscar/ |archive-date=August 