y)|mandrake root]] raw.  Mifumi's alternate personality irritates Kazuko, who plots to humiliate her, first soaking her school uniform, then dressing her in a robotic nurse's uniform that forces Hifumi into erotic poses while Kazuko takes pictures. Somehow Mifumi remembers Akio's name long enough to scream for help, but her personality is not restored until she eats the raw mandoragora.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 11\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = A Gorgeous Party!?\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Shuchinikurin!?\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u9152\u6c60\u8089\u6797\uff01\uff1f\n| Title_2             = Miya Explodes! Showdown at the Sand Castle.\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Miya-sama Sakuretsu! Suna no Arashi no Katorea Shiro desu~\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u30df\u30e4\u69d8\u70b8\u88c2\uff01\u7802\u306e\u5d50\u306e[[Cattleya|\u30ab\u30c8\u30ec\u30a2]]\u57ce\u3067\u3059\uff5e\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2005|6|12}}\n| ShortSummary        = The Koi Koi 7 fight their way through Miya's Cattleya Castle to reach Gentai, but this is all just practice for the real battle.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 12\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = A Sensational Incident!\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Ky\u014dtendochi??\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u9a5a\u5929\u52d5\u5730\uff1f\uff1f\n| Title_2             = What Do Two of You Cry Out in the Center of World!\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Sekai no Ch\u016bsin de, Futari de Issho ni Nani Yobu? desu~\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u4e16\u754c\u306e\u4e2d\u5fc3\u3067\u3001\u4e8c\u4eba\u3067\u4e00\u7dd2\u306b\u30ca\u30cb\u53eb\u3076\uff1f\u3067\u3059\uff5e\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2005|6|19}}\n| ShortSummary        = Having decided not to disband after all, the Gok\u014d 5 pick one last fight with Koi Koi 7.  Their poor timing results in Kano giving all 12 of them cleaning duty for punishment, but then all the girls in school start chasing Tetsuro, and Yayoi is abducted by two advanced Celonius cyborgs.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 13\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = Tropical Paradise!?\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Shib\u014d Y\u016bgi!?\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u6b7b\u4ea1\u904a\u622f\uff01\uff1f\n| Title_2             = Fight With Naked Bodies! the Decisive Battle Field Is Tora Tora Tora\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Saigo no Kib\u014d, Himitsu soshite\u2026\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u6700\u5f8c\u306e\u5e0c\u671b\u3001\u79d8\u5bc6 \u305d\u3057\u3066\u2026\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2005|6|26}}\n| ShortSummary        = The gate to the other world is open, and it appears to be some kind of tropical paradise.  Tetsuro frolics in the waves with Gentai and two other young girls.  Kano suns herself on the beach, and the Koi Koi 7 play in the sand.  Izuma and Subaru rub each other with suntan lotion.  Offshore a sinister submarine lurks: Gok\u014d 5 is at it again, but beats a strategic retreat when Otome gets wet. When Otome's unconscious body is beamed up by a UFO, everyone goes off in pursuit, but they are distracted by the discovery of an [[onsen]], where the decisive battle ultimately takes place.\n}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20081204080114/http://trinet.cata.jp/koikoi7/ Official Homepage] {{in lang|ja}} (Archived)\n*[https://archive.is/20060815225311/http://www.enokifilmsusa.com/library/koikoi_n.htm Enoki Films] (Archived)\n*{{Ann|manga|7494}}\n\n[[Category:2002 manga]]\n[[Category:2005 Japanese television series endings]]\n[[Category:Akita Shoten manga]]\n[[Category:Anime series]]\n[[Category:Anime series based on manga]]\n[[Category:Ecchi anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Harem anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dnen manga]]\n[[Category:Discotek Media]]\n[[Category:Works about hanafuda]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = Koi Koi Seven\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| ja_kanji        = \u3053\u3044\u3053\u30447\n| ja_romaji       = Koi Koi 7\n| genre           = [[Comedy]], [[drama]], [[Harem (genre)|harem]]\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = [[Morishige]]\n| publisher       = [[Akita Shoten]]\n| demographic     = ''[[Sh\u014dnen manga|Sh\u014dnen]]'', ''[[Seinen manga|Seinen]]''\n| magazine        = [[Champion Red]] <small>(2002\u22122006)</small><br>[[Champion Red|Champion Red Ichigo]] <small>(2007)</small>\n| first           = October 2002\n| last            = April 2007\n| volumes         = 9\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = tv series\n| director        = Yoshitaka Fujimoto\n| producer        = \n| writer          = \n| music           = \n| studio          = Studio Flag<br>Trinet Entertainment\n| network         = \n| first           = April 4, 2005\n| last            = June 26, 2005\n| episodes        = 13\n| episode_list    = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''''Koi Koi Seven'''''|\u3053\u3044\u3053\u30447}} is a Japanese [[manga]] series created by [[Morishige]]. The story features a fighting squad of six girls (Koi Koi Seven) belonging to the Gok\u014d Academy who fight daily to protect the Earth's peace and future, as well as the hopeless Tanaka Tetsuro. ''Koi Koi Seven'' was serialized in [[Akita Shoten]]\u2019s ''[[Champion Red]]'' line of magazines from 2002 to 2007. The series was adapted into a 13-episode [[anime]] television series which was broadcast between April 4, 2005 and June 26, 2005.\n\n==Plot==\nTetsuro Tanaka is transferred to Gokoh Academy full of high expectations. However, expectations fade with a bad premonition the moment he steps onto the campus and finds all the students except him are girls. A series of strange events fall upon him. Then, six girls who are called Koi Koi Seven appear as his guardians. Army combat helicopters and anti-tank guns attack Tetsuro for no particular reason as he tries to survive each day in the academy. Surrounded by many girls he gets into trouble every day because he often sees them naked, usually by mistake. In the dorm the same problem continues with the Koi Koi 7 team walking around the house in their underwear. On top of this, Celonious 28 also chases after him all the time because she wants to be with him. As well, Asuka Yayoi feels jealous of him because she loves him and she doesn't want him to hang around with other girls, which is very difficult because he is the only boy in the school and the girls are after him all the time. In general each girl of the Koi Koi 7 team has secret feelings for Tetsuro but they don't show them.\n\n== Characters ==\n;{{nihongo|Tetsuro Tanaka|\u7530\u4e2d \u54f2\u6717|Tanaka Tetsur\u014d}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Y\u016bki Tai]]}}\n:Tetsuro becomes the focus of attention for the entire school as he is the only male student. He can't seem to remember the reason why Yayoi always wants to be with him. He also comes to a difficult situation when by mistake he looks at the bra and panties of his roommates. Finally he has feelings for each girl of the Koi Koi Seven's team but he cannot show them for fear of the girls' anger.\n\n;{{nihongo|Yayoi Asuka|\u98db\u9ce5 \u30e4\u30e8\u30a4|Asuka Yayoi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Saori Got\u014d]]}}\n: The main heroine of the story. She is part of a group of girls who call themselves the \"Koi Koi 7\". She had apparently known Tetsuro when they were younger. She claims to have a reason for wanting to be with him all the time. She likes crab bread, a trait which is often exploited by Gokoh Five. She also has the ability to fly and has white angel like wings. However, sometimes she becomes annoying to Tetsuro which led him to ignore her.\n\n;{{nihongo|Sakuya Kazamatsuri|\u98a8\u796d \u30b5\u30af\u30e4|Kazamatsuri Sakuya}}\n:{{voiced by|Ayako It\u014d}}\n: She is one of Tetsuro's roommates. She is an expert at many firearms and often is seen pulling them out of nowhere (including a bazooka). She's the most talkative and the one that always gets on to Tetsuro. She calls Tetsuro <<kinky>> and tries to express her feelings for him with kinky ideas herself. She always feels comfortable and she doesn't mind walking around naked even if Tetsuro is in front of her. These make her the main sexy character in Tetsuro's imagination.  She also has a tendency to smoke and skip classes making others believe she is a delinquent.\n\n;{{nihongo|Miyabi Tsukuyomi|\u6708\u8aad \u30df\u30e4\u30d3|Tsukuyomi Miyabi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Akiko Kawase (actress)|Akiko Kawase]]}}\n:She is another roommate of Tetsuro. She can use her hair to form a nearly-impenetrable shield or as an attack weapon. She is very popular in the school even though she finds it annoying. In the anime her background remains a mystery, it only shows her cutting her wrist and blood is flowing out. She believes that Tetsuro is different from the other boys because he always cares for her. In other words, she also has feelings for him.  She also has expressed a lack of caring for the lives of the other Koi Koi Seven like grabbing them around the throat with her hair and pulling them along because they are too slow.\n\n;{{nihongo|Hifumi Inokai|\u732a\u98fc \u30d2\u30d5\u30df|Inokai Hifumi}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Kimiko Koyama]]}}\n:Another one of Tetsuro's roommates. Rivalling Otome for the most flat chest, she is normally calm until provoked. She is the only one who is stronger than Akiwo. She tends the school [[garden]] commonly and is generally good friends with Akiwo. She had been very unfair with Tetsuro while she knocked him down because he saw her butt by mistake.\n\n;{{nihongo|Akiwo Suzuka|\u9234\u9e7f \u30a2\u30ad\u30f2|Suzuka Akiwo}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Y\u016bko Gibu]]}}\n: Another one of Tetsuro's roommates. She is very busty and has orange hair. She has \"Superman-like\" powers like super strength and the ability to [[fly]]. But she has mentioned that she has not always been like this. She told Tetsuro that she used to be someone who was very weak and had to be rescued all the time. She explained that she kept telling herself that she should change. She is also a huge fan of \"Kinorangers\", which is most likely a Parody of the 1980 Super sentai series [[Denshi Sentai Denjiman]] since their suits resembles the Denjiman Suits.  She was the one to come up with the name Koi Koi 7. She believes that each person can become strong. So she felt proud of Tetsuro when he shot the kinky monster. After that she started to have feelings for him too.  She often goes off on her own.\n\n;{{nihongo|Otome Chono|\u8776\u91ce \u30aa\u30c8\u30e1|Chono Otome}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Y\u016bna Inamura]]}}\n: Another one of Tetsuro's roommates. She has a very calm personality which makes her less aggressive than the other girls in the group. In the anime she has been seen \"charging up\" using a plug during breakfast, also in the group she is the person who gives the orders and information to the rest of the group after analyzing the data. Otome's comments often include words like \"incomprehensible,\" making her \"robot-like.\" Later in the anime she is revealed to be a [[robot]]. Even though she is a robot, she still dreams and has feelings like the feelings she has for Tetsuro, even though she cannot even comprehend those feelings herself. However Tetsuro made her very happy saying to her that she is an absolutely normal girl.  She wears large ribbons in her hair.\n\n;Kozoma :(people who joined the school in their senior year) This group includes all six girls in the Koi Koi 7, plus Tetsuro.\n\n;{{nihongo|Yayoi Asuka (Celonius 28)|\u30a2\u30b9\u30ab\u30e4\u30e8\u30a4 (\u30bb\u30ed\u30cb\u30a2\u30b928\u53f7)|}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Nana Mizuki]]}}\n:A mysterious girl with an eyepatch. She believes that she is the real Yayoi that Tetsuro met in his past, due to being a part of a nationwide security system designed to watch and protect Yayoi and  Tetsuro. She was then rebuilt as a [[gynoid]] and through the events of the story was mostly destroyed. With all her memory erased she is rebuilt as a robot but in a much younger form (much like Otome as she is in her spare body), now called Gantai she has the mentality of a child. Early on she thought that nobody loved her, but Tetsuro changes her mind showing her that everyone loves her. After that she tries to take care of Tetsuro and make him happy. Voiced by [[Nana Mizuki]].\n\n;{{nihongo|Orie Kano|\u82b1\u7687 \u30f2\u30ea\u30a8|Kano Orie}}\n:{{voiced by|Akiko Kimura}}\n: The [[teacher]], who also lives in the student dorm with Tetsuro and the Koi Koi 7 girls. She had feelings for Tetsuro's father before he managed to open the heaven's door.  She is also a mechanic.\n\n;{{nihongo|Kong\u014d Higashikazuno|\u6771\u548c\u91ce \u91d1\u525b|Higashikazuno Kong\u014d}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Norio Wakamoto]]}}\n: The mysterious headmaster who has hidden knowledge about Tetsuro. His mission is to stop Tetsuro's father before he makes something bad.\n\n;{{nihongo|Miya Higashikazuno|\u6771\u548c\u91ce \u30df\u30e4|Higashikazuno Miya}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Tsubasa Otomiya]]}}\n: Grandchild of the school's founder. She is officious and self-important. She and her gang, the Gokoh Five, are constantly after Tetsuro.\n\n;{{nihongo|Hekusokazura no Kimi|\u5c41\u7cde\u8513\u306e\u541b}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Saki Nakajima (voice actress)|Saki Nakajima]]}}\n: Second in command at the Gokoh Five. She also has a secret personality as a spy in the school in order to watch Tetsuro's father movements.\n\n;{{nihongo|Kazuko Iidabashi|\u98ef\u7530\u6a4b \u548c\u5b50|Iidabashi Kazuko}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Rumi Abe]]}}\n: A member of the Gokoh Five. Very nervous.\n\n;{{nihongo|Chuko Asakusabashi|\u6d45\u8349\u6a4b \u4e2d\u5b50|Asakusabashi Ch\u016bko}}\n:{{voiced by|Kana Masaki}}\n: A member of the Gokoh Five.\n\n;{{nihongo|Yoko Suidobashi|\u6c34\u9053\u6a4b \u6d0b\u5b50|Suidobashi Y\u014dko}}\n:{{voiced by|Yoshimi Ninomiya}}\n: A member of the Gokoh Five. More logical and sensitive.\n\n;{{nihongo|Isuzu Yamada|\u5c71\u7530 \u30a4\u30b9\u30ba|Yamada Isuzu}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Miyu Matsuki]]}}\n: A student who is head over heels in love with Satou. She wrote a lesbian book.\n\n;{{nihongo|Subaru Satou|\u4f50\u85e4 \u30b9\u30d0\u30eb|Sat\u014d Subaru}}\n:{{voiced by|Miho Miyagawa}}\n: Another student who is head over heels in love with Yamada. At first she didn't want to have a relationship with Yamada but in the end she loves her.\n\nTetsuro's Father is a mysterious man who is furious because the council turned down his research. He tries to get revenge by robots such as Celonious 28.\n\n== Media ==\n\n=== Manga ===\n''Koi Koi Seven'' was first serialized in [[Akita Shoten]]\u2018s ''[[Champion Red]]'' magazine in 2002. The individual chapters were subsequently released in nine compiled [[tank\u014dbon]] volumes, the last of which was released March 20, 2007.<ref name=\"volume 9\" />\n\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n| WithTitle  = no\n| OneLanguage = yes\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 1\n| RelDate         = March 13, 2003<ref name=\"volume 1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.akitashoten.co.jp/comics/detail/comic_id/472/ |title=Koi Koi 7 vol. 1 at AkitaShoten.co.jp|publisher=[[Akita Shoten]] |accessdate=2012-08-12 |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n| ISBN            = 4-253-23000-8|ISBN_note=<ref name=\"volume 1\" />\n}}\n\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 2\n| RelDate         = August 21, 2003<ref name=\"volume 2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.akitashoten.co.jp/comics/detail/comic_id/5587/ |title=Koi Koi 7 vol. 2 at AkitaShoten.co.jp|publisher=[[Akita Shoten]] |accessdate=2012-08-12 |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n| ISBN            = 4-253-23001-6|ISBN_note=<ref name=\"volume 2\" />\n}}\n\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 3\n| RelDate         = March 25, 2004<ref name=\"volume 3\">{{cite web |url=http://www.akitashoten.co.jp/comics/detail/comic_id/