e. A [[Super Sentai|sentai]]-[[mecha]] battle ensues. At the end of a tiring day, Tetsuro retires to his school dorm, only to discover that he is housed with Yayoi and the Koi Koi Seven. His teacher Ms. Kano is the dorm supervisor.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 02\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = Girls Bravo!\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Sh\u014djo Banzai (G\u0101ruzu Burab\u014d)!\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u5c11\u5973\u4e07\u6b73(\u30ac\u30fc\u30eb\u30ba\u30d6\u30e9\u30dc\u30fc)\uff01\n| Title_2             = Get Wet, Get Washed Away! It's Miya-Sama's Revenge\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Yuretenagarete! Gyakushu no Miya-sama desu~\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u63fa\u308c\u3066\u6d41\u308c\u3066\uff01\u9006\u8972\u306e\u30df\u30e4\u69d8\u3067\u3059\uff5e\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2005|4|10}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fed up with the girls fighting over him, to say nothing of them flaunting their underwear, Tetsuro calls his father and asks to be transferred to another school, but is told to stick it out.  Kano overhears and reports the conversation to the headmaster.  At school, Miya [[Animal trapping#Snares|snares]] and ties him [[Suspension bondage|suspended]] over the pool.  Tetsuro is forced to watch from this position as the girls compete for him, first swimming a medley relay, then wrestling \"Mongolian-style\" (the objective being to strip the pants from one's opponent), and finally in a volleyball game.  The Koi Koi Seven win every event: witnessing their determination, Tetsuro admits that there is something to be said for girls who go to such extent for his sake.  Still not satisfied, Miya reactivates her mecha, merging all five into a super-robot, only to be  humiliated by a malfunction.\n\nCelonius 28 makes her first appearance, floating alone in the pool, calling Tetsuro's name.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 03\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = Special Effects Are On Fire!\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Tokusatsu Jimoe (Geki Faiy\u0101)!\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u7279\u64ae\u6fc0\u71c3(\u30b2\u30ad\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30e4\u30fc)\uff01\n| Title_2             = Beyond Akiwo\u2019s Heart\u2026What?\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Akiwo, Kokoro no Mukou ni\u2026desu~\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u30a2\u30ad\u30f2\u3001\u5fc3\u306e\u5411\u3053\u3046\u306b\u2026\u3067\u3059\uff5e\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2005|4|17}}\n| ShortSummary        = Garbed as one of her favorite cartoon heroes, Akiwo battles the nefarious Sailor-Bloomer Mask, a vacuum-equipped villain who sucks the [[Japanese school uniform#Sailor outfit|uniforms]] off of unsuspecting high school girls, leaving them screaming in their underwear.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 04\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = Beautiful Flowers Are Soon Picked!\n| TranslitTitle_1     = Bijinhakumei!?\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u7f8e\u4eba\u8584\u547d\uff01\uff1f\n| Title_2             = What Is Otome's Daydream?\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Otome-chan wa Nani o Yumemiru? desu~\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u30f2\u30c8\u30e1\u3061\u3083\u3093\u306f\u4f55\u3092\u5922\u307f\u308b\uff1f\u3067\u3059\uff5e\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2005|4|24}}\n| ShortSummary        = It rains.  Otome gets wet.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 05\n| NumParts            = 2\n| Title_1             = Splendides! Concours De Beaut\u00e9\n| TranslitTitle_1     = G\u014dkakenran Bakunyu Taikai\n| NativeTitle_1       = \u8c6a\u83ef\u7d62\u721b\u7206\u4e73\u5927\u4f1a\n| Title_2             = Traansperce Le Ciel D'Odaiba\n| TranslitTitle_2     = Odaiba no Sora o Tsuranuite desu~\n| NativeTitle_2       = \u304a\u53f0\u5834\u306e\u7a7a\u3092\u3064\u3089\u306c\u3044\u3066\u3067\u3059\uff5e\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2005|5|1}}\n| ShortSummary        = Miya hosts a swimsuit com