y Moore]]\n|UD\n|8\n|04/11/1999\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Idaho}} [[Worley, Idaho]], [[United States]]\n|align=left|{{small|78-73, 79-72, 80-71.}}\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|{{small|11-0}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Bruce Bellocchi]]\n|TKO\n|4\n|17/06/1999\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Idaho}} [[Worley, Idaho]], [[United States]]\n|align=left|{{small|Referee stopped the bout at 2:57 of the fourth round.}}\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|{{small|10-0}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Louis Monaco|Louis \"The Facelifter\" Monaco]]\n|UD\n|6\n|06/05/1999\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Washington}} [[Tacoma, Washington]], [[United States]]\n|align=left|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|{{small|9-0}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Terry Verners]]\n|TKO\n|1\n|02/11/1998\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Arizona}} [[Phoenix, Arizona]], [[United States]]\n|align=left|{{small|Referee stopped the bout at 2:19 of the first round after Verners had been knocked down twice in the bout.}}\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|{{small|8-0}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Samoa}} [[Tui \"The Smokin' Samoan\" Toia]]\n|KO\n|1\n|12/05/1998\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Missouri}} [[Kansas City, Missouri]], [[United States]]\n|align=left|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|{{small|7-0}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Derrick Ryals]]\n|DQ\n|3\n|09/04/1998\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Arizona}} [[Phoenix, Arizona]], [[United States]]\n|align=left|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|{{small|6-0}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Felton Hamilton]]\n|SD\n|6\n|19/12/1997\n|align=left|{{flagicon|New York}} [[New York City]], [[United States]]\n|align=left|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|{{small|5-0}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Thomas Allen (boxer)|Thomas Allen]]\n|KO\n|3\n|14/11/1997\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Arizona}} [[Phoenix, Arizona]], [[United States]]\n|align=left|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|{{small|4-0}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|United States}} [[Anthony Curry]]\n|UD\n|4\n|28/05/1997\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Nevada}} [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], [[United States]]\n